Peru Stocks: Edegel, Aceros Arequipa, Ferreyros, Candente, IRL

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-03-17T20:39:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/peru-stocks-edegel-aceros-arequipa-ferreyros-candente-irl.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:11 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index fell 1.1 percent to 20,758.13. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index dropped 0.8 percent to 2,888.71.  Industrial stocks slumped on investor concerns the Japanese
crisis will derail the global economic recovery, said Arlen Lahura, a trader at Lima-based brokerage Coril SAB.  Edegel SA (EDEGELC1 PE), the Peruvian unit of  Spain ’s
Endesa SA, plunged 5.1 percent to 1.85 soles. Corp. Aceros
Arequipa SA (CORAREI1 PE), the Lima-based steelmaker, fell 2.7
percent to 3.25 soles.  Cementos Pacasmayo SAA (CPACASC1)  (CPACASC1 PE), the
Hochschild Group’s cement producer, fell 3.4 percent to 6.33
soles.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1)  (FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor
for Caterpillar Inc., fell 2.6 percent to 3.80 soles.  Copper and gold miners gained after the metals advanced for
a second day in New York.    Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, jumped 5.3 percent to 20 cents.  Candente
Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration company, rose 4.8
percent to $1.75.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K. minerals
explorer with a gold mine in Peru, gained 3.5 percent to $1.50.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest copper producer,
rose 2 percent to $40.50.  To contact the reporter on this story:  Alex Emery  in  Lima  at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  